hackathon-description-text: HSHacks II is the return of the premier high school hackathon. More than 1400 high school students from around the country come to the Silicon Valley to turn ideas into a reality, all in 24 hours. With world class mentors, food, space, and more, you’re in for an amazing time. We welcome students of all hacking ability.
hackathon-eligibility: You must be currently enrolled in high school and have submitted your hack to challengepost by 1PM to qualify for a prize.
hackathon-requirements:
Please submit a description of what your project does and screenshots (videos are optional). 
All submissions due at 1 PM!
hackathon-rules:
All code must be written at the hackathon.
4 to a team. 
Have fun!
Submit by 1!

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Dell Venue Pro tablets for the team
Unity Pro Licenses for the team
